channel.title: Rundown of how to get a server public
channel.description: I have tried this for a good while and I keep coming to a dead end. Ok, I've portforwarded, I have No-Ip, and I have utorrent, but when I try to log on my server, it says "error connecting to server, please try again." but I've also noticed that when I go to compiler and run it, it says "server is already in use." so, mayeb I've changed the Ip in the wrong place or something. Maybe my computer is blocking the port 43594 connection, Idk what to do...

item.title: Rundown of how to get a server public
item.dc:creator: @CoonHunter CoonHunter
item.description:
@CoonHunter wrote:

The IP has no belonging in your server. Also, is your IP dymanic (assigned to your computer, and that is all your computer uses), or is it static (gets a new one every connect). It needs to be assigned to our computer via router. If its not, that could just be your problem.

Also, about the “server already in use”, go to your task-manager and exit javaw.exe and/or java.exe

Read full topic
